00:24:46,612 --> 00:24:48,572
You are

273
00:24:49,448 --> 00:24:51,450
a great master,

274
00:24:51,575 --> 00:24:53,619
you are very important for me.

275
00:24:54,453 --> 00:24:56,413
You teach ten lessons

276
00:24:56,622 --> 00:24:59,416
to workers in my factory.

277
00:25:00,584 --> 00:25:02,586
I pay you in cash,

278
00:25:03,587 --> 00:25:05,589
2,000 euros a lesson

279
00:25:07,466 --> 00:25:08,634
for ten lessons.

280
00:25:09,551 --> 00:25:12,638
We work together,
but no one knows it,

281
00:25:13,639 --> 00:25:15,557
just the two of us.

282
00:25:17,476 --> 00:25:19,436
I need your help.

283
00:25:20,604 --> 00:25:22,439
Think it over.

284
00:25:26,610 --> 00:25:29,488
- What's the cloth like?.
- Come and see.

285
00:26:03,397 --> 00:26:04,565
I've got nothin'!

286
00:26:04,648 --> 00:26:06,608
Don't move!

287
00:27:09,671 --> 00:27:12,549
They must have gone over to his side,

288
00:27:13,425 --> 00:27:16,470
or they'd have arrested
me first and then those other guys.

289
00:27:16,595 --> 00:27:19,598
Believe me?. All of them were there
when I called you.

290
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:22,476
I said: Check out this car,
it's suspect.

291
00:27:22,518 --> 00:27:24,478
This stuff here is ours.

292
00:27:24,603 --> 00:27:26,480
My gun!

293
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:31,401
Check this stuff out,
there should be fifty-six.

294
00:27:33,445 --> 00:27:35,531
Good, Toto, this is for you.

295
00:27:39,618 --> 00:27:41,662
How can I get working with you?.

296
00:27:42,454 --> 00:27:44,456
We'll let you know.

297
00:27:46,416 --> 00:27:48,627
- Did you turn off the water?.
- Of course!

298
00:27:49,461 --> 00:27:51,630
- Can I help out?.
- No, you'll get wet.

299
00:27:52,464 --> 00:27:53,590
Doesn't matter!

300
00:27:54,508 --> 00:27:56,426
Come and see.

301
00:27:56,510 --> 00:27:58,470
Careful not to slip.

302
00:27:59,513 --> 00:28:03,475
- Is it coming from the well?.
- No, I think it's from the pipe.

303
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:06,478
Careful, water's coming in.

304
00:28:07,604 --> 00:28:10,399
See if you can close it.

305
00:28:10,482 --> 00:28:12,526
It's closed,
but it's the pipe that...

306
00:28:18,657 --> 00:28:20,659
I'd give you a hand, but...

307
00:28:22,494 --> 00:28:23,620
What a great day!

308
00:28:24,413 --> 00:28:26,456
Push it all in one direction.

309
00:28:32,588 --> 00:28:35,424
I thought I'd be having coffee!

310
00:28:35,507 --> 00:28:38,594
- Nice coffee, huh?.
- I'll have some next time.

311
00:28:46,518 --> 00:28:48,478
Totore, things okay?.

312
00:28:49,646 --> 00:28:52,566
- Can I say hi?.
- No, you gotta leave.

313
00:28:52,649 --> 00:28:55,402
Go down with these bags!

314
00:28:56,486 --> 00:28:58,447
You have to move!

315
00:28:59,531 --> 00:29:01,533
Ma'am, go around the other way.

316
00:29:01,575 --> 00:29:04,536
- What's going on?.
- Everything's fine, leave.

317
00:29:24,598 --> 00:29:25,641
Lucia?.

318
00:29:56,505 --> 00:29:57,589
Come closer.

319
00:29:58,590 --> 00:30:01,426
- What's your name?.
- Luigi.

320
00:30:02,636 --> 00:30:05,472
- Are you scared?.
- No.

321
00:30:05,556 --> 00:30:07,641
- Sure?.
- No.

322
00:30:08,475 --> 00:30:09,601
We'll see.

323
00:30:10,644 --> 00:30:13,605
- Are you strong?.
- Yeah!

324
00:30:14,565 --> 00:30:16,608
Let's see how strong you are.

325
00:30:20,571 --> 00:30:22,489
Why are you shaking?.

326
00:30:23,657 --> 00:30:25,409
No?.

327
00:32:26,613 --> 00:32:29,533
- See how strong this kid is.
- Come closer!

328
00:32:36,665 --> 00:32:39,501
- Are you scared?.
- Yes.

329
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:58,478
Now you're a man.

330
00:33:16,663 --> 00:33:18,624
Nothin'! Everything's okay!

331
00:33:19,666 --> 00:33:23,504
When I did my piercing,
I got an infection.

332
00:33:23,587 --> 00:33:25,464
Let's see.

333
00:33:26,507 --> 00:33:28,467
You went and did it there?.

334
00:33:29,635 --> 00:33:32,513
- I'd like to have it on my eyebrow.
- Stinks.

335
00:33:32,596 --> 00:33:34,598
It's nicer there, you're right.

336
00:33:36,683 --> 00:33:38,644
It's gonna rain.

337
00:33:44,525 --> 00:33:45,609
Everything's okay!

338
00:33:45,692 --> 00:33:47,694
A car's coming!

339
00:33:49,613 --> 00:33:51,532
It went in!

340
00:33:53,617 --> 00:33:55,577
It's going in!

341
00:33:56,495 --> 00:33:58,497
Check out this other one!

342
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:02,543
Everything's okay!

343
00:34:33,615 --> 00:34:36,618
Sorry I'm late, the Councilman,
City Hall, the traffic...

344
00:34:37,536 --> 00:34:39,621
- My father.
- How do you do.

345
00:34:43,542 --> 00:34:46,503
I'm glad he's with you
you're a good person.

346
00:34:46,628 --> 00:34:48,589
He's in your care.

347
00:34:48,714 --> 00:34:50,591
He's a clever guy.

348
00:34:52,509 --> 00:34:53,635
I don't doubt that but...

349
00:34:53,719 --> 00:34:56,555
- Having work is important to him.
- Of course.

350
00:34:56,597 --> 00:34:59,516
I tried so hard
to find him work in Naples...

351
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:02,644
- Where do you work?.
- In the hospital, intensive care.

352
00:35:03,478 --> 00:35:05,522
A bad division.

353
00:35:06,565 --> 00:35:10,652
I tried to get him in,
but I have no connections.

354
00:35:11,487 --> 00:35:13,489
He's all set now.

355
00:35:13,572 --> 00:35:16,492
You did something no one else did.

356
00:35:16,575 --> 00:35:18,660
I thank you, you raised him well.

357
00:35:18,744 --> 00:35:20,662
Have you always worked in Naples?.

358
00:35:21,455 --> 00:35:23,540
No, also in Trieste, Udine,

359
00:35:24,458 --> 00:35:26,543
- Venice...
- That's where we're going.

360
00:35:26,627 --> 00:35:29,588
I told him about Venice.

361
00:35:30,547 --> 00:35:33,675
He's excited, it's his first time.

362
00:35:34,510 --> 00:35:37,638
Dad, we have a plane.

363
00:35:38,472 --> 00:35:40,474
Did you bring some things?.

364
00:35:40,599 --> 00:35:42,643
What's that, your gym bag?.

365
00:35:43,644 --> 00:35:46,522
- Goodbye.
- He's in your care.

366
00:36:05,666 --> 00:36:09,503
- What do you pay for disposal?.
- Today I'm paying 50.

367
00:36:09,586 --> 00:36:10,712
Your offer?.

368
00:36:11,547 --> 00:36:13,507
We can halve your costs,

369
00:36:13,590 --> 00:36:15,509
25 cents a kilo.

370
00:36:15,592 --> 00:36:17,511
That's good,

371
00:36:17,594 --> 00:36:19,555
but is it all "clean",
like they say in the United States?.

372
00:36:19,638 --> 00:36:21,598
Since it's toxic waste,

373
00:36:21,682 --> 00:36:24,476
certification,
storage and transportation.

374
00:36:26,645 --> 00:36:29,606
- Is there a contract to look over?.
- Of course.

375
00:36:33,610 --> 00:36:35,529
In case you're wondering,

376
00:36:35,612 --> 00:36:37,614
the disposal cycle

377
00:36:37,698 --> 00:36:40,492
goes to the disposal area
in Marcianise.

378
00:36:40,534 --> 00:36:42,494
I'm telling you in fairness.

379
00:36:42,578 --> 00:36:44,663
Thank you for the information,

380
00:36:45,497 --> 00:36:47,708
but my only concern
is that it's "clean".

381
00:36:48,500 --> 00:36:50,544
You can rest assured of that.

382
00:36:50,627 --> 00:36:52,629
We can dispose of all the waste

383
00:36:52,754 --> 00:36:54,715
that you produce in a year.

384
00:36:55,507 --> 00:36:56,633
Eight hundred tons.

385
00:36:58,468 --> 00:36:59,511
It's not a problem.

386
00:36:59,595 --> 00:37:00,721
That's a lot.

387
00:37:04,766 --> 00:37:06,685
My concern is disposal.

388
00:37:07,519 --> 00:37:09,646
We serve various companies,
you can check.

389
00:37:10,647 --> 00:37:12,608
I already have!

390
00:37:13,609 --> 00:37:15,527
Don't worry.

391
00:37:16,653 --> 00:37:19,573
As far as I can see,
there's maximum transparency.

392
00:37:19,615 --> 00:37:21,450
Absolutely.

393
00:37:23,619 --> 00:37:26,663
- The warehouses at Teverola?.
- We use them for tires.

394
00:37:27,498 --> 00:37:28,540
Exactly.

395
00:37:28,707 --> 00:37:31,627
Will we put the tannery waste
in the quarry?.

396
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:34,463
- Don't talk foolishness.
- Where then?.

397
00:37:34,546 --> 00:37:36,590
Check the European catalogue.

398
00:37:38,634 --> 00:37:40,552
Here they are, 04.

399
00:37:41,512 --> 00:37:43,639
The ones in red,
are among the most dangerous.

400
00:37:44,515 --> 00:37:47,643
"Exhausted degreasing baths
with solvents, no liquid phase."

401
00:37:48,477 --> 00:37:49,686
No, no good.

402
00:37:51,647 --> 00:37:53,607
Then 4-11:

403
00:37:53,690 --> 00:37:56,568
"Waste containing halogenated
compounds from operations

404
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:58,570
of manufacturing and finishing."

405
00:37:58,654 --> 00:38:00,572
These are good.

406
00:38:00,656 --> 00:38:04,451
It's stuff the earth absorbs,
we'll mix it with compost.

407
00:38:04,535 --> 00:38:05,619
Fertilizer!

408
00:38:08,497 --> 00:38:11,458
All that leaves is
Milan's sweeping refuse,

409
00:38:11,542 --> 00:38:13,460
that's 60 trucks.

410
00:38:14,545 --> 00:38:17,464
- The quarries at San Felice?.
- They're too small.

411
00:38:17,548 --> 00:38:19,508
I don't think so, look.

412
00:38:19,716 --> 00:38:21,593
Let me see.

413
00:38:27,599 --> 00:38:29,643
They're too small
and they're shallow,

414
00:38:30,727 --> 00:38:32,604
they're no good.

415
00:38:43,699 --> 00:38:47,494
Yes... I've got
ten contracts out of ten.

416
00:38:51,498 --> 00:38:52,624
Is he near you?.

417
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:56,587
Put him on.

418
00:38:57,462 --> 00:38:58,630
I'll talk to him.

419
00:39:20,694 --> 00:39:23,530
I told him, everything's okay.

420
00:39:36,585 --> 00:39:39,505
- Do you like traveling?.
- Sure!

421
00:39:39,755 --> 00:39:41,673
We'll take more trips.

422
00:39:50,682 --> 00:39:52,684
Everyone here works in boats?.

423
00:39:53,519 --> 00:39:56,522
Everyone, firemen, ambulances...

424
00:39:57,648 --> 00:40:00,692
- Funerals.
- I've already seen two.

425
00:40:01,527 --> 00:40:03,529
Even the dead go by boat!

426
00:40:25,676 --> 00:40:27,678
Wow, they've got so many!

427
00:40:33,517 --> 00:40:34,560
Steady me.

428
00:41:24,651 --> 00:41:26,570
There's nothing here.

429
00:41:40,709 --> 00:41:42,628
Nothing?.

430
00:41:42,711 --> 00:41:44,588
Are you sure?.

431
00:42:09,738 --> 00:42:11,573
Oh God!

432
00:42:11,615 --> 00:42:13,575
Look what's here!

433
00:42:20,624 --> 00:42:22,668
See?. It's like you said!

434
00:42:25,671 --> 00:42:27,548
Look here!

435
00:42:27,673 --> 00:42:29,550
A Beretta 93!

436
00:42:29,633 --> 00:42:31,510
A Kalashnikov!

437
00:42:31,677 --> 00:42:33,679
See if they're loaded.

438
00:42:34,596 --> 00:42:36,682
- Check.
- It's unloaded.

439
00:42:51,613 --> 00:42:53,532
Look, an M12!

440
00:42:53,740 --> 00:42:55,701
This is the 921.

441
00:42:56,493 --> 00:42:57,619
That bearded bum!

442
00:42:57,703 --> 00:42:59,746
We'll see how
he blows my head off!

443
00:43:00,789 --> 00:43:03,750
Enough for Casale di Principe!
Everybody!

444
00:43:05,544 --> 00:43:07,588
Won't blow my head off now, eh?.

445
00:43:11,717 --> 00:43:13,677
Should I put two in?.

446
00:43:15,637 --> 00:43:17,556
And Nikita's?.

447
00:43:17,639 --> 00:43:19,558
And the 38?.

448
00:43:35,616 --> 00:43:38,702
- Want to see how I can shoot?.
- Show me!

449
00:43:39,703 --> 00:43:41,580
Show me!

450
00:43:42,623 --> 00:43:44,583
Aim there!

451
00:44:18,742 --> 00:44:20,577
I hit it!

452
00:44:36,593 --> 00:44:38,637
We'll blow
the Colombians' heads off!

453
00:44:46,687 --> 00:44:48,564
That's good.

454
00:44:52,734 --> 00:44:54,611
Everything okay?.

455
00:44:59,616 --> 00:45:01,577
With love and feeling.

456
00:45:14,548 --> 00:45:16,717
- What is it?.
- Your wife's on the phone.

457
00:45:17,551 --> 00:45:18,760
Tell her not to wait up.

458
00:45:19,553 --> 00:45:21,680
Don't get tired out, need anything?.

459
00:45:22,556 --> 00:45:23,682
No, thanks.

460
00:45:23,765 --> 00:45:25,726
- You'll lock up?.
- Yes.

461
00:45:26,643 --> 00:45:27,644
Goodnight.

462
00:45:50,751 --> 00:45:52,586
Xian?.

463
00:46:26,578 --> 00:46:27,704
I have been waiting for you.

464
00:46:29,748 --> 00:46:32,751
- I got lost.
- I am happy you came.

465
00:46:46,557 --> 00:46:47,641
Please sit down.

466
00:46:50,644 --> 00:46:52,688
We are cooking fish.

467
00:47:02,614 --> 00:47:04,533
I've already eaten.

468
00:47:05,576 --> 00:47:07,619
Try a typical Chinese dish.

469
00:47:08,537 --> 00:47:09,663
Okay?.

470
00:47:15,711 --> 00:47:18,589
Just cooked, it is good.

471
00:47:18,630 --> 00:47:20,549
Meat with bell peppers.

472
00:47:20,632 --> 00:47:22,593
I've already eaten.

473
00:47:25,637 --> 00:47:26,722
Taste.

474
00:47:27,556 --> 00:47:29,516
We use chopsticks.

475
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:31,643
- I don't know how to use them.
- Try!

476
00:47:34,646 --> 00:47:36,607
I am pleased,

477
00:47:36,648 --> 00:47:38,692
we have a little toast.

478
00:47:39,776 --> 00:47:42,529
We go to the factory.

479
00:47:49,745 --> 00:47:51,622
Why not?.

480
00:47:55,626 --> 00:47:57,586
I put a pillow in here.

481
00:47:57,711 --> 00:47:59,588
It's dangerous.

482
00:48:00,714 --> 00:48:04,551
I already told you,
no one can know, just us.

483
00:48:04,718 --> 00:48:06,720
It's better for both of us.

484
00:48:07,554 --> 00:48:11,600
- Won't I need air?.
- No, there's an opening.

485
00:48:12,643 --> 00:48:15,604
I'll open the front window,
so air will come in.

486
00:48:17,648 --> 00:48:19,525
Forgive me.

487
00:48:21,568 --> 00:48:22,736
Are we sure?.

488
00:48:24,738 --> 00:48:27,741
It is best for both of us,
because it is dangerous.

489
00:48:30,702 --> 00:48:33,539
- Does air come through here?.
- Yes.

490
00:48:33,747 --> 00:48:35,749
And I'll open the window too.

491
00:49:38,562 --> 00:49:40,564
Please come in, Mr. Pasquale.

492
00:49:41,773 --> 00:49:43,734
All are waiting for you.

493
00:49:46,695 --> 00:49:48,655
All are very happy.

494
00:50:03,587 --> 00:50:05,714
I told them who you are
and all are happy.

495
00:50:08,592 --> 00:50:10,511
What a nice factory!

496
00:50:10,677 --> 00:50:12,721
More than 80 people.

497
00:50:54,680 --> 00:50:56,640
I'm moved.

498
00:51:00,644 --> 00:51:02,604
What can I say?.

499
00:51:03,730 --> 00:51:05,732
To do this work

500
00:51:06,775 --> 00:51:09,528
you need lots of patience...

501
00:51:14,783 --> 00:51:16,702
...and lots of love.

502
00:51:22,749 --> 00:51:24,710
For the first lesson...

503
00:51:27,629 --> 00:51:29,673
...I'll cut out a bodice.

504
00:51:37,639 --> 00:51:38,724
Let's begin.

505
00:51:49,651 --> 00:51:52,571
You must place patterns carefully.

506
00:51:58,744 --> 00:52:00,746
Spread the cloth well...

507
00:52:23,644 --> 00:52:25,604
Maria, are you asleep?.

508
00:52:30,609 --> 00:52:32,694
Where have I been, in China?.

509
00:52:35,656 --> 00:52:37,658
They were all bowing to me.

510
00:52:39,743 --> 00:52:41,578
Master!

511
00:52:41,703 --> 00:52:44,581
They called me "master"!

512
00:52:49,586 --> 00:52:52,589
- Did you know the Chinese can cook?.
- The Chinese?.

513
00:52:52,714 --> 00:52:54,675
Darn right!

514
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:57,594
They cooked a delicious bass!

515
00:53:01,598 --> 00:53:02,766
There were boxes everywhere

516
00:53:03,600 --> 00:53:05,561
and they put me in the trunk!

517
00:53:06,687 --> 00:53:08,689
Both coming and going.

518
00:53:12,568 --> 00:53:13,777
I need some sleep.

519
00:53:17,573 --> 00:53:18,657
Here.

520
00:53:19,575 --> 00:53:21,618
I have to sleep a few hours.

521
00:53:25,622 --> 00:53:27,666
What's this money?.

522
00:53:38,677 --> 00:53:40,637
Where did you get it?.

523
00:53:40,762 --> 00:53:42,723
I have to sleep.

524
00:53:45,684 --> 00:53:47,561
Help me understand.

525
00:53:47,686 --> 00:53:49,688
I talked to my son this morning,

526
00:53:49,771 --> 00:53:52,608
he said: "Mom I'm leaving,

527
00:53:52,774 --> 00:53:54,735
I'm going to be a secessionist."

528
00:53:55,777 --> 00:53:57,613
Really?.

529
00:54:01,617 --> 00:54:03,577
What did you say?.

530
00:54:03,744 --> 00:54:05,662
He's convinced,

531
00:54:06,622 --> 00:54:08,665
he said: "We're great,

532
00:54:08,749 --> 00:54:12,669
we'll win the war,
the others are nobodies".

533
00:54:12,711 --> 00:54:15,756
War?. A bunch of morons
warring against us?.

534
00:54:16,673 --> 00:54:18,634
You have to stop him.

535
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:21,720
This side is the right side.

536
00:54:23,597 --> 00:54:25,682
Have you seen what's happening?.

537
00:54:25,807 --> 00:54:27,768
There are killings every day.

538
00:54:29,645 --> 00:54:32,606
Don't say anything to anybody,
not even your husband.

539
00:54:33,774 --> 00:54:35,692
Who'd ever tell him!

540
00:54:37,736 --> 00:54:40,739
When he gets out, what'll he do?.
Father and son will kill each other?.

541
00:54:41,573 --> 00:54:43,617
No, because your son
will stay right here.

542
00:54:45,702 --> 00:54:47,746
They'll all come to a bad end.

543
00:54:52,626 --> 00:54:54,628
Do you feel so sure about that?.

544
00:54:54,670 --> 00:54:55,796
