I've warned them more than once.

807
01:23:46,944 --> 01:23:48,904
I can't consider them kids anymore.

808
01:23:49,905 --> 01:23:51,865
They have to die, that's final!

809
01:23:51,990 --> 01:23:55,869
You're right,
but first let's tell the families.

810
01:23:55,953 --> 01:23:57,871
I don't know who they are.

811
01:23:59,873 --> 01:24:02,835
Will you take care of it?.

812
01:24:02,960 --> 01:24:05,003
I'll handle it!

813
01:24:32,781 --> 01:24:33,991
Toto, is that you?.

814
01:24:39,997 --> 01:24:42,958
- What happened to Silvana?.
- In the storeroom.

815
01:24:59,016 --> 01:25:01,810
How come it's so dark?.

816
01:25:01,894 --> 01:25:03,854
Why are you in the dark?.

817
01:25:03,896 --> 01:25:05,772
It's okay like this.

818
01:25:06,023 --> 01:25:07,858
Your change.

819
01:25:09,985 --> 01:25:12,905
- The bread?.
- There wasn't any.

820
01:25:12,988 --> 01:25:15,908
- What'll we eat?.
- There's pasta.

821
01:25:18,911 --> 01:25:21,788
- Take your change.
- It's for you.

822
01:25:31,882 --> 01:25:34,009
Why did you put her
in the storeroom?.

823
01:25:34,843 --> 01:25:36,804
She's fine where she is.

824
01:25:37,012 --> 01:25:39,848
She's just an animal!

825
01:26:50,919 --> 01:26:52,963
Come here a minute,
I have to talk to you.

826
01:26:54,882 --> 01:26:56,842
Don't come out, it's dangerous.

827
01:26:56,967 --> 01:26:58,969
Come on, no one can see you.

828
01:27:02,890 --> 01:27:04,850
What are you doing, you're going?.

829
01:27:07,978 --> 01:27:09,771
Listen to me!

830
01:27:10,022 --> 01:27:12,816
They said I have to leave.

831
01:27:12,983 --> 01:27:14,985
I have to leave my house.

832
01:27:15,903 --> 01:27:17,863
I can't do anything.

833
01:27:17,946 --> 01:27:19,907
I'm not leaving!

834
01:27:20,908 --> 01:27:22,868
Come here a minute!

835
01:27:28,916 --> 01:27:32,002
Tell those friends of yours,
I'm not leaving!

836
01:27:33,837 --> 01:27:35,881
Tell those nice people!

837
01:27:36,006 --> 01:27:39,843
I won't betray my son
and I'm not moving from here!

838
01:27:41,887 --> 01:27:43,847
Not coming in for coffee?.

839
01:27:43,931 --> 01:27:45,808
Run off, run away!

840
01:28:24,847 --> 01:28:25,973
Hello, accountant.

841
01:28:26,890 --> 01:28:27,891
Please come in.

842
01:28:29,017 --> 01:28:31,979
Why this sudden call?.

843
01:28:32,813 --> 01:28:33,939
You're worrying me.

844
01:28:34,815 --> 01:28:36,817
The designers pay me after 60 days,

845
01:28:36,900 --> 01:28:38,944
I have a little money,

846
01:28:39,027 --> 01:28:41,780
but this wasn't the agreement.

847
01:28:41,864 --> 01:28:43,907
Money isn't the problem.

848
01:28:44,992 --> 01:28:46,869
What is it then?.

849
01:28:46,952 --> 01:28:48,871
It seems

850
01:28:49,913 --> 01:28:51,957
the problem is in your own house.

851
01:28:53,000 --> 01:28:54,918
In my house?.

852
01:28:55,002 --> 01:28:56,962
What problem is it?.

853
01:28:58,046 --> 01:28:59,965
One of your associates,

854
01:29:01,800 --> 01:29:02,885
Pasquale Del Prete,

855
01:29:03,010 --> 01:29:04,845
has sold out to the Chinese.

856
01:29:14,980 --> 01:29:16,857
We're done.

857
01:29:20,819 --> 01:29:21,945
The finishing touches...

858
01:29:30,871 --> 01:29:32,831
I never doubted.

859
01:29:51,975 --> 01:29:53,852
Everything okay?.

860
01:29:56,939 --> 01:29:59,942
Remember the first time
I put you to work in the factory?.

861
01:30:00,025 --> 01:30:01,944
You were just a kid.

862
01:30:03,987 --> 01:30:05,030
Right.

863
01:30:14,915 --> 01:30:17,000
- Everything alright?.
- Yes.

864
01:30:40,858 --> 01:30:43,902
Tell him to go slower, not too fast.

865
01:30:57,875 --> 01:30:59,001
Well done, Giulia.

866
01:30:59,877 --> 01:31:00,961
She's good.

867
01:31:31,909 --> 01:31:33,869
In the morning I do Tai Chi.

868
01:31:33,952 --> 01:31:34,953
Really?.

869
01:31:35,829 --> 01:31:38,040
- It's nice.
- It is good for your health.

870
01:31:38,874 --> 01:31:40,918
It is like in China.

871
01:31:41,919 --> 01:31:45,839
When you go to the park
in the morning, it is full of people

872
01:31:46,965 --> 01:31:48,884
old people too.

873
01:31:49,843 --> 01:31:51,845
All doing Tai Chi.

874
01:31:51,929 --> 01:31:53,055
Everyone

875
01:31:54,056 --> 01:31:56,850
Iikes the culture of Tai Chi.

876
01:31:58,852 --> 01:32:01,021
It's a tradition of Chinese culture.

877
01:32:01,855 --> 01:32:03,941
When will you do egg rolls for me?.

878
01:32:58,036 --> 01:32:59,830
Wait up.

879
01:33:01,874 --> 01:33:04,960
I spoke to the doctors,
you'll soon be released.

880
01:33:11,925 --> 01:33:13,886
Damn you,

881
01:33:14,011 --> 01:33:15,929
you really goofed up.

882
01:33:17,973 --> 01:33:21,852
They loved the models,
they've asked for more...

883
01:33:21,935 --> 01:33:23,854
You knew everything.

884
01:33:23,937 --> 01:33:26,023
That's how I saved your life.

885
01:33:26,982 --> 01:33:29,860
Those people don't kid around.

886
01:33:29,985 --> 01:33:31,862
Leave me alone.

887
01:33:31,945 --> 01:33:35,866
You should thank me,
those guys will kill you.

888
01:33:35,908 --> 01:33:37,951
You and I pulled through.

889
01:33:38,035 --> 01:33:40,996
- Find another tailor.
- Why do you say that?.

890
01:33:41,872 --> 01:33:44,917
- I want to be alone.
- How can I do this without you?.

891
01:33:45,000 --> 01:33:46,877
I really don't care.

892
01:33:47,002 --> 01:33:50,881
- After all I've done for you.
- What have you done for me?.

893
01:33:50,923 --> 01:33:54,009
I took you off the streets,
I fed you for years.

894
01:33:54,843 --> 01:33:57,805
-You've used me since I was a kid.
- Don't say that!

895
01:33:58,931 --> 01:34:02,059
When you're better,
come see me, I'll give you a raise.

896
01:34:04,061 --> 01:34:07,898
Rosa, give me that bike,
I have to go.

897
01:35:33,066 --> 01:35:35,068
No admittance here,

898
01:35:35,861 --> 01:35:37,029
that's it.

899
01:35:51,084 --> 01:35:53,045
Want to give up?.

900
01:35:53,879 --> 01:35:56,006
Are we meat for the slaughter house?.

901
01:36:04,848 --> 01:36:06,809
Let's shoot,
we'll rack up corpses too.

902
01:36:06,934 --> 01:36:08,018
Corpses?.

903
01:36:09,019 --> 01:36:12,815
- I'm not moving without orders.
- What orders?.

904
01:36:12,940 --> 01:36:14,983
We don't know how to move.

905
01:36:16,985 --> 01:36:18,946
We don't know anything.

906
01:36:22,032 --> 01:36:24,827
Do we have to keep taking it?.

907
01:36:24,952 --> 01:36:27,037
Do we have to wait for orders?.

908
01:36:30,040 --> 01:36:32,000
Let's rack up corpses.

909
01:36:32,084 --> 01:36:35,921
What are we waiting for,
to be put down one by one?.

910
01:36:39,883 --> 01:36:42,010
If we don't move, nothing will change

911
01:36:42,094 --> 01:36:44,054
No use feeling depressed.

912
01:36:45,973 --> 01:36:47,975
We all have to be convinced.

913
01:36:48,058 --> 01:36:50,894
But without orders, I'm not moving.

914
01:36:53,063 --> 01:36:55,023
This is open war,

915
01:36:55,858 --> 01:36:57,818
you mustn't think about anyone.

916
01:36:57,943 --> 01:37:00,988
- Who do we kill?.
- Let's begin in our area.

917
01:37:02,030 --> 01:37:04,032
From our own stronghold.

918
01:37:04,867 --> 01:37:06,994
We don't know who's with us
and who's against us,

919
01:37:07,077 --> 01:37:09,079
who do we make pay?.

920
01:37:09,872 --> 01:37:12,916
Where do you think
the order to kill came from?.

921
01:37:13,000 --> 01:37:14,084
Think!

922
01:37:15,878 --> 01:37:17,838
Where did it come from?.

923
01:37:18,046 --> 01:37:20,883
- From there of course.
- From our own area.

924
01:37:20,966 --> 01:37:22,926
She betrayed us.

925
01:37:23,010 --> 01:37:25,053
We don't touch women.

926
01:37:25,846 --> 01:37:26,972
Don't yell!

927
01:37:27,973 --> 01:37:29,933
What are you saying?.

928
01:37:33,061 --> 01:37:36,940
Don't take it out on someone
no part of this, but the son.

929
01:37:37,065 --> 01:37:40,861
- How do we find him?.
- His mother's in our district.

930
01:37:40,903 --> 01:37:42,863
It was her son who killed Gaetano.

931
01:37:42,988 --> 01:37:44,948
Let's think what we'll do.

932
01:37:45,949 --> 01:37:47,993
We could use the kid.

933
01:37:48,869 --> 01:37:50,913
He's the only one who can get to her.

934
01:37:52,039 --> 01:37:53,957
He brings her shopping,

935
01:37:54,041 --> 01:37:56,084
he's in good with the woman...

936
01:37:57,002 --> 01:37:59,004
So, if we have to do it

937
01:37:59,087 --> 01:38:01,048
we'll need his help.

938
01:38:03,884 --> 01:38:05,886
Toto, what do you think you'll do?.

939
01:38:07,012 --> 01:38:09,056
Are you with us or against us?.

940
01:38:15,896 --> 01:38:17,856
What do you say?.

941
01:38:19,024 --> 01:38:20,984
Are you with us or not?.

942
01:38:22,903 --> 01:38:25,864
- We'll see what we can do.
- No, "we'll see".

943
01:38:25,906 --> 01:38:27,950
Either you're with us
or you're against us,

944
01:38:28,909 --> 01:38:30,869
one or the other.

945
01:38:30,911 --> 01:38:34,873
If you're against us you can't leave,
we can't trust you.

946
01:38:34,957 --> 01:38:37,042
It can't have been her.

947
01:38:37,960 --> 01:38:39,920
This is our decision,

948
01:38:40,003 --> 01:38:41,964
you have to be with us.

949
01:38:42,047 --> 01:38:45,050
That's what we say,
you don't need to think.

950
01:38:49,972 --> 01:38:51,932
What are you going to do?.

951
01:38:52,975 --> 01:38:56,019
- We'll see.
- I said no "we'll see".

952
01:39:11,910 --> 01:39:12,953
Come on down.

953
01:39:13,036 --> 01:39:14,997
I have to tell you something!

954
01:39:16,957 --> 01:39:18,834
No, come down!

955
01:39:19,960 --> 01:39:22,004
Hurry, I have to leave!

956
01:40:58,976 --> 01:41:00,060
Sit down!

957
01:41:36,972 --> 01:41:38,932
You've known me for years,

958
01:41:39,016 --> 01:41:41,059
you know what I've always done.

959
01:41:42,978 --> 01:41:44,855
I brought the money.

960
01:41:44,938 --> 01:41:46,982
I brought it to your family too.

961
01:41:48,942 --> 01:41:50,986
I did it because I was ordered to.

962
01:41:55,949 --> 01:41:57,951
War isn't for me.

963
01:41:58,118 --> 01:42:00,954
But you're in it, know that?.

964
01:42:02,998 --> 01:42:03,999
Yes.

965
01:42:04,124 --> 01:42:05,918
So?.

966
01:42:06,084 --> 01:42:07,878
You tell me.

967
01:42:07,961 --> 01:42:09,838
What can I tell you?.

968
01:42:13,091 --> 01:42:15,886
What did you come here for?.

969
01:42:17,888 --> 01:42:19,056
To talk to you.

970
01:42:19,932 --> 01:42:21,058
About what?.

971
01:42:24,937 --> 01:42:26,897
I want to save myself.

972
01:42:26,980 --> 01:42:29,066
You'll have to buy your life,

973
01:42:29,900 --> 01:42:31,860
I won't give it to you.

974
01:42:36,073 --> 01:42:38,033
What I did there,

975
01:42:39,034 --> 01:42:41,036
I can do for you here.

976
01:42:41,912 --> 01:42:43,956
We don't need money-carriers,

977
01:42:43,997 --> 01:42:47,042
we have to score,
kill people, and we need money.

978
01:42:48,085 --> 01:42:49,962
You're wasting your time.

979
01:42:53,048 --> 01:42:54,967
You're more dead than alive.

980
01:42:55,050 --> 01:42:57,928
But we were brothers before.

981
01:42:58,011 --> 01:42:59,012
Before!

982
01:42:59,096 --> 01:43:02,015
Then they started
messing around with shit.

983
01:43:06,937 --> 01:43:08,981
Our relatives were good people...

984
01:43:09,940 --> 01:43:11,984
so they killed them!

985
01:43:13,944 --> 01:43:15,070
So, don't come asking

986
01:43:15,904 --> 01:43:17,072
to pass to the other side.

987
01:43:17,906 --> 01:43:19,950
We have to score, kill,

988
01:43:20,033 --> 01:43:21,994
and we need money.

989
01:43:22,911 --> 01:43:24,079
If not, you die,

990
01:43:24,913 --> 01:43:26,915
because you're part of the war.

991
01:43:26,957 --> 01:43:28,959
You bring money and I kill people,

992
01:43:29,084 --> 01:43:31,920
we're the same, you and me,
in this war.

993
01:43:33,046 --> 01:43:35,007
- I understand.
- You understand.

994
01:43:45,893 --> 01:43:47,060
Wait a moment.

995
01:44:17,132 --> 01:44:19,009
Everything okay?.

996
01:44:21,136 --> 01:44:23,013
And you?.

997
01:44:30,020 --> 01:44:31,897
That's four.

998
01:44:42,074 --> 01:44:44,034
Face on the table!

999
01:44:44,868 --> 01:44:46,078
Done?.

1000
01:44:47,037 --> 01:44:48,080
Let's go!

1001
01:44:56,046 --> 01:44:57,881
Come on out!

1002
01:44:58,090 --> 01:45:00,050
Lucky, eh?.

1003
01:46:23,008 --> 01:46:24,968
That's poison.

1004
01:46:26,136 --> 01:46:28,096
What'd he say?.

1005
01:46:28,931 --> 01:46:32,059
My father wants to say the dumping
you're doing on our land

1006
01:46:32,893 --> 01:46:34,019
isn't garbage.

1007
01:46:34,895 --> 01:46:36,021
It's poison.

1008
01:46:36,146 --> 01:46:38,065
It's not garbage?.

1009
01:46:39,942 --> 01:46:41,109
You heard right.

1010
01:46:41,944 --> 01:46:43,070
Don't worry.

1011
01:46:43,946 --> 01:46:46,949
A year's gone by with this dumping?.

1012
01:46:48,075 --> 01:46:50,994
So far,
all we've done is pay our debts.

1013
01:46:52,079 --> 01:46:53,121
Just barely.

1014
01:46:53,914 --> 01:46:57,084
- Euro.
- I understand, Don Raffaele.

1015
01:46:59,962 --> 01:47:02,089
Everything costs double in euro.

1016
01:47:03,006 --> 01:47:04,091
And so?.

1017
01:47:05,884 --> 01:47:07,136
We need something more.

1018
01:47:09,012 --> 01:47:11,932
These are the prices,
explain it to your kids,

1019
01:47:12,015 --> 01:47:14,977
if I do it for you,
I have to do it for everyone.

1020
01:47:15,060 --> 01:47:17,020
Don't put me
in a difficult situation.

1021
01:47:17,104 --> 01:47:20,983
Okay, if you give us more,
everyone has to get more.

1022
01:47:21,024 --> 01:47:22,985
So, little can be done.

1023
01:47:23,068 --> 01:47:25,112
But, we barely make ends meet,

1024
01:47:25,946 --> 01:47:27,948
we can't go on like this.

1025
01:47:28,031 --> 01:47:29,992
We were thinking,

1026
01:47:31,076 --> 01:47:34,037
is it possible to do more dumping?.

1027
01:47:36,081 --> 01:47:37,916
Euro...

1028
01:47:38,083 --> 01:47:40,085
More dumping?.

1029
01:47:40,919 --> 01:47:43,881
We have another piece of land
for other dumping sites.

1030
01:47:43,964 --> 01:47:45,132
Near here?.

1031
01:47:46,049 --> 01:47:47,926
Around here.

1032
01:47:47,968 --> 01:47:49,928
More dumping we do,

1033
01:47:50,053 --> 01:47:52,055
faster the ground gets filled.

1034
01:47:52,139 --> 01:47:54,933
You have another piece of land?.

1035
01:47:55,934 --> 01:47:58,103
- Near here?.
- Further on.

1036
01:47:58,937 --> 01:48:01,940
This other land
would be more convenient,

1037
01:48:01,982 --> 01:48:04,985
it's bigger and trucks
can get in easier.

1038
01:48:06,111 --> 01:48:07,905
But...

1039
01:48:09,907 --> 01:48:11,867
Still 100 euros per dumping.

1040
01:48:11,992 --> 01:48:13,911
What do you mean 100 euros!

1041
01:48:14,036 --> 01:48:15,996
Don't speak out of turn.

1042
01:48:16,038 --> 01:48:18,040
- He can't increase!
- Who said so?.

1043
01:48:18,916 --> 01:48:20,918
We'll increase the trucks.

1044
01:48:22,002 --> 01:48:25,047
You have to increase
the price of each dumping.

1045
01:48:26,089 --> 01:48:27,966
Want to lose everything?.

1046
01:48:28,050 --> 01:48:30,093
They have nowhere else to turn.

1047
01:48:30,886 --> 01:48:31,929
Excuse me.

1048
01:48:32,012 --> 01:48:33,889
Don't worry.

1049
01:48:35,140 --> 01:48:37,100
Alright, now we'll reach...

1050
01:48:42,022 --> 01:48:43,941
an agreement.

1051
01:48:44,024 --> 01:48:46,068
Give him a glass of water.

1052
01:48:46,151 --> 01:48:48,111
I'll do it, don't worry.

1053
01:48:57,955 --> 01:48:58,956
Luca!

1054
01:49:06,046 --> 01:49:08,090
You have to clean up this field!

1055
01:49:09,049 --> 01:49:10,884
I'm not Luca.

1056
01:49:11,009 --> 01:49:12,970
Do a little work.

1057
01:49:13,053 --> 01:49:14,972
My name's Roberto.

1058
01:49:17,057 --> 01:49:19,101
This field is such a mess.

1059
01:49:20,060 --> 01:49:21,937
All such a mess.

1060
01:49:22,980 --> 01:49:24,148
Ma'am, it's raining.

1061
01:49:25,899 --> 01:49:27,025
Should I stop?.

1062
01:49:27,151 --> 01:49:29,069
Come out of there.

1063
01:49:31,947 --> 01:49:33,907
I'll take you inside.

1064
01:49:34,158 --> 01:49:36,034
I'll be right along.

1065
01:49:36,160 --> 01:49:38,078
They've made ditches here,

1066
01:49:38,954 --> 01:49:40,914
someone should come

1067
01:49:41,039 --> 01:49:42,958
to fill them.

1068
01:49:55,971 --> 01:49:57,014
Let's go!

1069
01:50:09,067 --> 01:50:10,986
What beautiful peaches, thank you!

1070
01:50:11,069 --> 01:50:13,030
I'll take them to the kids.

1071
01:50:13,155 --> 01:50:15,115
See how beautiful they are!

1072
01:50:16,158 --> 01:50:17,993
